Up for sale are 100 pieces of PMC .223 Rem cases converted to 300 AAC Blackout. I throw a few extras in just in case I mis-counted. Believed to be once fired and that's how I bought them. Not crimped so I cannot confirm this though. They have been fully processed and are ready for loading. About 10% were selected and verified with a Wilson case gauge. 5 pieces were measured with caliper and separately bagged. Pic shows cases you will actually receive, not a file photo. As you can see, these take a bit of work to get just right and I pride myself on the finished product.

Steps taken:
1. Cut at shoulder 
2. Full length sized and deprimed
3. Trimmed with Lee case length gauge (1.750/1.752)
4. Case mouth chamfered inside and out
5. Ran through sizing die again.
6. Crimps removed
7. Primer pockets cleaned
8. Tumbled
9. Polished
